    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`win_viewport` is very slow when scrolling many lines with 'breakindent'\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. With `NVIM_LOG_FILE` set, run:\r\n```sh\r\nnvim --clean -c \"setlocal breakindent | call setline(1, repeat([repeat(' foo', &columns)], 50000)) | call feedkeys('G', 'n') | call timer_start(0, {_ -> execute('qa!')})\"\r\n```\r\n2. Nvim takes a long time to exit, with `NVIM_LOG_FILE` showing that a `win_viewport` event after the `G` takes very long produce:\r\n```\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 nvim.488708.0 state_enter:96: input: <G>\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 nvim.488708.0 UI: raw_line (+47 times...)\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 nvim.488708.0 UI: win_viewport\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 nvim.488708.0 UI: grid_cursor_goto\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 nvim.488708.0 UI: mode_info_set\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 nvim.488708.0 UI: mode_change\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 nvim.488708.0 UI: mouse_on\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 nvim.488708.0 UI: flush\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 ?.488706   receive_msgpack:295: ch 3: parsing 2035 bytes from msgpack Stream: 0x61d000000c88\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 nvim.488708.0 inbuf_poll:458: blocking... events_enabled=0 events_pending=0\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 nvim.488708.0 UI: raw_line\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 nvim.488708.0 UI: flush\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.547 nvim.488708.0 UI: raw_line\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:30.548 ?.488706   receive_msgpack:295: ch 3: parsing 52 bytes from msgpack Stream: 0x61d000000c88\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:43.345 nvim.488708.0 UI: win_viewport\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:43.345 nvim.488708.0 UI: raw_line\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:43.349 nvim.488708.0 UI: raw_line (+36 times...)\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:43.349 nvim.488708.0 UI: win_viewport\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:43.349 nvim.488708.0 UI: grid_cursor_goto\r\nDBG 2023-07-03T07:53:43.349 nvim.488708.0 UI: flush\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNvim exits instantly like Nvim v0.8.x or Vim\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0-dev-617+g2d40f5e84\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.28.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
